```

But then it becomes more interesting: the typescript server sends a request to the IDE `_typescript.rename`. The IDE logs that as unsupported and the typescript server then sends an error notification, that the IDE does not support the request. This needs more work and maybe tie in from the typescript plugin in NetBeans itself.

@matthiasblaesing

> But then it becomes more interesting: the typescript server sends a request to the IDE _typescript.rename.

I guess that's because the server wants the `age` field to be renamed, so that the field and the getter names don't clash. At least that's what happens in other editors such as VS Code and Eclipse. In them, `age` would be renamed to `_age` automatically.
